# .cursorrules

## Project: MediTriage AI — Mobile App (Patient)
## Stack: React Native + Expo Managed, JavaScript only, Zustand, Supabase

## Purpose
Patient-facing mobile app for AI-powered medical triage.
Patients describe symptoms via voice/text/image → AI analyzes →
triage result (LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH) → saved to Supabase → doctor sees it on web dashboard.

## Architecture Rules
- Expo Router for navigation (file-based, in src/app/)
- ALL Supabase calls in src/features/[feature]/services/
- NO direct AI calls from any component or hook
- ALL AI calls via Supabase Edge Functions (ai.service.js only)
- State: Zustand only (auth.store.js, triage.store.js)
- Animations: Reanimated 3 only (never Animated from RN core)
- Use 'expo install' not 'npm install' for Expo packages

## Folder Mapping
- Screens: src/app/(patient)/ and src/app/(auth)/
- Feature components: src/features/[feature]/components/
- Hooks: src/features/[feature]/hooks/
- Services: src/features/[feature]/services/
- Shared UI: src/components/ui/
- Store: src/store/
- Utils: src/utils/
- Theme: src/styles/theme.js

## Navigation Structure
- (auth) group: splash, login, signup, verify, role-select, patient-setup
- (patient) group with tabs: home, triage/, reports, profile
- Triage is a nested stack inside (patient): start → session → result → sos

## Supabase Tables
- patient_profiles: read/write patient data
- triage_cases: INSERT new cases, SELECT history (patient's own only)
- ai_feedback: SELECT only (read doctor's note on past cases)

## Risk Levels (EXACT strings — must match web dashboard)
- "HIGH" → red, Emergency SOS auto-shown, haptic heavy × 3
- "MEDIUM" → amber, see doctor soon, haptic medium × 1
- "LOW" → green, home care, haptic light × 1

## Message Shape (triage_cases.messages jsonb array)
{ role: 'user'|'assistant', content: string, type: 'text'|'voice'|'image', timestamp: ISO8601 }

## Env Variables (EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix required for client access)
- EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
- EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

## DO NOT
- Use TypeScript
- Use bare React Native (Expo Managed only)
- Call Gemini directly from app
- Use AsyncStorage directly (use expo-secure-store for sensitive data)
- Use StyleSheet colors inline — always import from theme.js
- Implement anything requiring native Xcode/Android Studio setup
